    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-29T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-29T13:00:00-05:00" n="704"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10895a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="77" xml:id="d704fn77">The same as No. 273 to the Ambassador
                        In Japan.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-29T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 29, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>325. According to an Associated Press report from Shanghai of October 29 the
                    German Ambassador was stated to be in Nanking acting as a mediator and messenger
                    carrying proposed Japanese peace terms.<note n="78" xml:id="d704fn78">See
                        Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Documents on German Foreign Policy,
                            1918–1945</hi>, series D, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 733
                        ff.</note> The report states further that the German Ambassador recently
                    spent a week in Shanghai in conference with the Japanese Ambassador and other
                    high officials.</p>
                <p>The Department has received information to this same general effect attributed to
                        Suma.<note n="79" xml:id="d704fn79">Japanese Counselor of Embassy in the
                        United States.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Please telegraph urgently what you can discreetly ascertain in regard to this
                    report and your estimate as to its significance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
